originalLintResult.source:
<form id='chart-navigation-form'>

        <label for='chart-select'>
          {{#if this.chartGroup.showChartsTogether}}
            Change group:
          {{else}}
            Change chart:
          {{/if}}
        </label>

        {{#if this.chartNavigationPrevious}}
          {{! Ember transition is slower (about 2x?) than a regular link and breaks the chart dropdown. }}
          <BasicLink
            @route='charts.show'
            @model={{this.chartNavigationPrevious.chart.id}}
            @query={{this.chartLinkQueryParams}}
            title={{this.chartNavigationPrevious.display}}
          >
            ⮜
          </BasicLink>
        {{/if}}

        <select name='chart' id='chart-select' {{on 'change' this.goToChart}}>
          {{#each this.chartNavigationChoices as |navChoice|}}
            <option
              value='{{navChoice.chart.id}}'
              selected={{if (eq navChoice.chart.id @model.chart.id) 'selected'}}
            >
              {{navChoice.display}}
            </option>
          {{/each}}
        </select>

        {{#if this.chartNavigationNext}}
          <BasicLink
            @route='charts.show'
            @model={{this.chartNavigationNext.chart.id}}
            @query={{this.chartLinkQueryParams}}
            title={{this.chartNavigationNext.display}}
          >
            ⮞
          </BasicLink>
        {{/if}}

      </form>
originalLintResult.message: If multiple landmark elements (or elements with an equivalent role) of the same type are found on a page, they must each have a unique label.
